overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was visually
  lacking. The agent undertook a comprehensive review, starting with an analysis
  of existing styles and identifying areas for improvement such as the generic
  color palette, plain backgrounds, and basic form elements. The approach
  involved implementing a new calming, sleep-themed color palette, redesigning
  the main questionnaire form layout with subtle background effects and an
  enhanced progress indicator, and updating core UI components like checkboxes,
  radio buttons, and sliders for a more polished look. All questionnaire
  sections were systematically updated to reflect the new design, replacing old
  gray-boxed groupings with refined card-style elements. During the process, a
  console error related to null input values was identified and fixed by
  modifying the  component to safely handle  values. Finally, based
  on user feedback, the agent addressed remaining aesthetic inconsistencies,
  specifically in the report section's card headers and various alert
  components, by introducing theme-based utility classes and ensuring all colors
  aligned with the new sleep theme. The outcome is a visually cohesive,
  professional, and calming application experience.
